BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Banned Book Club 2026: Dignity & Freedom to Read
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260519T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260519T170000
UID:d107db91b06bdab6872d2236a4789a88@mobilize.us
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mobilize-uploads-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/u
 ploads/event/Mobilize%20Graphics%20%286%29_20260316171716457215.png
DESCRIPTION:As classroom censorship bills sweep state legislatures\, schoo
 ls are removing books by and about LGBTQ people\, BIPOC\, and other margin
 alized groups from curriculums and libraries at an unprecedented rate. Las
 t year\, more than 111 bills aiming to limit discussions about race and ge
 nder in the classroom have been passed or introduced in state legislatures
 . These efforts effectively erase voices\, histories and lived experiences
  from students’ K-12 education. This summer the ACLU of Indiana is hosti
 n
LOCATION:Virtual event
URL:https://www.mobilize.us/acluin/event/922098/
X-SOURCE:Indivisible Central Indiana (Mobilize)
